This paper focuses on poisoning attacks to graph-based recommender systems, which involves techniques from machine learning, optimization, and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which covers topics related to network analysis, recommendation systems, and security. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which suggests it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, since the paper discusses security attacks, it could also be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
